    'body' => 'According to what I have found in my CT/MT library the Solomani (Alien 
Module 6) were using jumps within the solar system after they discovered 
the jump drive in 2087 AD. From what I understand this was a regular jump 
1 drive; since the nearest star is at jump 2, the intrasystem use was
rather natural.

According to Alien Module 7, instead, the Hivers developed a faulty jump 
drive 1 (melting after few uses, less than 10) and only 400 years later
did they discover the regular jump 1 drive. Due to the jump cost I
suspect they did not use their faulty drive for microjumps.

Apparently the Vilani also had problems with the jump drive, which was 
regular but based on a faulty theoretical understanding (thus resulting 
in very slow development of higher than jump-2 drives, Starship Operator\'s
Manual).

I have also a recollection of some race developing a drive that would only
do microjumps, but I haven\'t been able to recover the information. Does 
anybody else remember it?. A microjump-only drive, if smaller and with
smaller fuel requirements could actually be quite handy.

The natural MT guess for such a jump-0 drive would be:
1 jump unit (13.5 kl, 27 tons, 3 Mcr) per 100 tons. The fuel usage
would be the regular 67.5 kl per jump unit. Thus a microjump drive
would be half the size and require half the fuel of a regular jump 1.


                             Max


