The Imperium DID build mid-rift refuelling points (yes, this is canonical).
It has been stated that Dulinor and/or Lucan destroyed them during the 
laughingly-labelled "Final War".
(I call it this because: a. no war is ever the final one, and b. it has
nothing on the real "Final War", 300,000 years earlier).

I am not at home, so cannot supply the page reference - I think it was
at least mentioned in the Arrival Vengance adventure, as the ship is
trying to get back home. I am sure that it is mentioned earlier, though.

In xboat 348, Tony Reynolds <cctony@tp.backbone.olemiss.edu> asks:
>Is there any explanation ever given for the positioning of the Octagon and
>the base below? A book/page reference would be nice.

No. The only thing you can guess at, reading between the lines, is that
the original Octagon guy was stranded on the same planet. It says
that he underwent some sort of "conversion" after his rescue, becoming
fanatical that no-one would ever suffer as he did - but what if it was
due to the sight of the base? He could have built the Octagon above it - or,
even more likely, he FOUND the Octagon and used it as a model for all
the others! The guy could even have changed his story to say that he was
marooned elsewhere - diverting attention away from the base.

