Well, you\'re right, to an extent. From the looks of things, the Himalayas 
were the last spot on Earth to remain as dry land. A few of your 
assumptions, however, weren\'t on the mark...

It looks like some disaster did occur to cause the melting of the polar 
ice caps, which did indeed result in a reversal of the earth\'s magnetic 
poles (something which has happened in the past, w/ or w/out natural 
disaster). As a result, the \'map\' (a tattoo on a young girls back) proves 
to have the wrong co-ordinates unless you do some reversing around.

OK, it\'s not exactly a clear explanation, but I don\'t really want to 
spoil the movie for anyone who actually sees it. My biggest complaint is 
that there is no way in hell you can row an oil tanker.

