    'from' => 'ggoffin@igc.apc.org',
    'year' => 1995,
    'index' => 'ab623',
    'topic' => 'starship self destruct; nuclear missiles',
    'body' => 'No doubt these questions have come up before I joined the
list, so if someone will point me at the right archive
bundle, I suppose that I can figure out ftp.

1.  Starship self-destruct 

I assume that naval-type vessels will have self-destruct
capabilities (as in the Classic Star Trek episode, Let
That Be Your Last Battlefield). The most efficient
destructive methods that I can imagine are (1) programmed
jump failure and (2) fusion power plant explosion. Can the
fusion power plant be made to explode (like a hydrogen
bomb, or in some other way)?  If so, what about the fusion
plant of your 15-year-old\'s grav scooter? (I\'m just
shuddering at the thought of certain fifteen year olds with
whom I went to high school armed with nuclear weapons --
well, one of them did end up on nuclear subs, and we\'re all
still here.) 

Suggestions on the extent of damage to nearby ships
(destruction of boarding parties and their mother ships
would sort of an anticipatory revenge function of the
self-destruct function) are also solicited.

2.  Nuclear missiles

What are the explosive parts of starship (or other) nuclear
weapons made of?  Uranium? Plutonium? Hydrogen?  Other
materials?  I suppose that the answer varies somewhat by
tech level -- U at TL6-7, Pu/H at TL8-9, etc.  What will be
used at higher tech levels (Cf is mentioned in Striker,
e.g.)?  

Will my sensor officer be able to scan a battle-damaged 
ship and say, "radiospectroscopy indicates ytterbium -- and 
the Zhodani are known to be using ytterbium warheads on 
their anti-ship missiles!"?

Thanks
--Glenn
