In actual fact, I meant HMS Antelope. Both ships were struck by bombs during 
the air attacks of 23 May 1982 and both were moved into San Carlos Water 
where attempts were made to defuse the bombs.

The bombs on HMS Argonaut were successfully defused. One of the bombs on HMS 
Antelope went off, killing one of the bomb-disposal men and starting a fire 
in the machine spaces in the stern of the ship.
The fire raged out of control while the ship\'s company were abandoning ship. 
By lucky chance, the last of the ship\'s company had left the ship ten 
minutes before the fire set off the Seacat (SAM) missiles in the after 
ready-use magazine. This was the spectacular picture which was transmitted 
around the world.
The fires eventually reached the other bomb the next day (24th May) and 
detonated that, blowing the ship in half and sinking her.

Sorry about that, but it was 13 years ago and memories are imprecise.

Dave

