31/7-95 Matthew S. Harelick wrote:

>What is the explanation for how teleportation on an orbital
>scale is performed?
>
>Can be interpreted as psionically going through a small
>segment of jumpspace?
>
>How about psionically causing oneself to matter
>transport?

How do you explain psionics? Is there something canonical
anywhere? I\'ve never seen it, but then again, I\'ve only
played Traveller since 1987 :-) Every little gadget or
technology has been detailed in Traveller, except for
psionics, it seems. But it would be nice to have an idea
about how it works.

How about psionics working via sub-atomic particles
called psions? :-) They probably don\'t have any mass,
moves at the speed of light and can be controlled by the
mind.

Thus telepathy would be an exchange of psions containing
information; telekinesis would be remote manipulation of
object via psions; teleportation would be the conversion
of oneself into psions, which are then moved to another
place and converted back again; claivonyance could be
something like a psion-based radar: You send out psions
to a specific place, and they return with information;
awareness is simply manipulation of one\'s own body with
psions.

Is this far out? Maybe, but how do you explain psionics?
These are just some thougts - I\'m open for better
explanations. It\'s just nice to know things like, how fast do
psionics work? If you do clairvoyance on a ship in orbit,
will there be a delay?

With psions moving at lightspeed, psionics won\'t be
possible/practical at interplanetary (let alone interstellar)
distances. This is - I *think* - in accordance with canon. It
seems like I once read somewhere, that psionics couldn\'t
be used at interplanetary distances, but I don\'t really
remember.

Comments, anyone?

Mark Seemann
ms@oem.dk
