    'topic' => 'Iridium bde report',
    'body' => 'I have been silent for a while on the Iridium bde business
since I was writing a GNU C++ program to find the effective
performance of the various units in a way not influenced by
human factors or chance.

The program implements MT ground cbt rules. The environment was a desertic 
one, without forests, broken ground etc. With this program I ran 1000
simulated battles at the battalion level and 600 at the brigade level.
Each battalion sized cbt group fought 400 battles, each brigade 300
battles. The Gamma Fast Armoured cbt grp is a version of the Gamma
Armoured Cbt Grp equipped with CGTs rather than MBTs.

No Meson Gun Boats were used.

The results are the following:

Battalion level:
                    Cost      Victories      Mean Loss      Victories/Gcr
Delta Cav. sqdn:  3494 Mcr      304       2.1 Gcr/battle       87.0
Gamma Armoured:   3610 Mcr      279       1.7 Gcr/battle       77.3
Gamma Fast Arm.:  3610 Mcr      230       2.5 Gcr/battle       63.7
Beta (3 grps):    3780 Mcr      157       2.5 Gcr/battle       41.5 
Gamma Mechan.:    2520 Mcr       30       2.2 Gcr/battle       11.9

It is interesting to note that in the simulations run by players the
Gamma Mechanized grp has actually defeated both the Delta cav sqdn and
the Gamma Armoured grp.

Brigade level:
               Cost      Victories      Mean Loss       Victories/Gcr
Delta rgt:  10482 Mcr       245        7.8 Gcr/battle     23.4
Gamma bde:   8984 Mcr       236        5.7 Gcr/battle     26.3
Beta bde*2:  9270 Mcr        78        8.4 Gcr/battle      8.4
Alpha bde:   7810 Mcr        41        6.7 Gcr/battle      5.2

It would seem that the "standard" 57th century NATO units (e.g. the
Gamma bde and the Delta rgt) are superior both in terms of absolute
effectiveness and in terms of cost effectiveness to the other units.
One should note, however, that both Beta and Alpha were effectively
mechanized units with a significantly smaller ratio of tanks to
infantry. It is possible that they would be much more effective in a
non desertic environment. This is also shown by the ineffectiveness of
the Gamma Mechanized cbt grp compared to the other battalions.

Note also the enormous losses experienced by all units.

More data than anybody may want to see can be found in:
http://astro.sns.it/~mstiavel/Traveller


----
