    'index' => 'ab644',
    'body' => 'This should be the final post on the Iridium bde TL 14 ground combat 
experiment (unless somebody arises new questions..). The vehicles
used, order of battle etc are as usual on 
http://astro.sns.it/~mstiavel/Traveller.

The combat simulation program allows one to specify the defensive 
attitude for each single platoon level unit. 

To explore the effect of changing this factor I have run another 1900 
engagements at the battalion level and 300 at the brigade level.

It turns out that extreme behaviour (ie very defensive or very aggressive) 
appears more convenient than intermediate behaviour. In addition very 
aggressive attitudes seem to be the most convenient for all unit types.

The most remarkable effect of this change of attitude is on
the Beta bde. Both at the combat group level and at the
(double) brigade level, Beta gains enormously in effectiveness.

The Beta bde when moving aggressively is equivalent to the Gamma
bde (also moving aggressively) and beats any other brigade.

Moreover all unit types in offensive attitude appear to be able to beat any 
other type in non offensive attitude.



