Hope you don\'t mind me chopping off your suggestions, but I just wanted
to save on some bandwidth.

Anyway, the answer to this question was answered in one of the issues
of either the Traveller\'s Digest or the Megatraveller\'s Journal.  I
can\'t remember which issue off the top of my head.  If someone reminds
me, I\'ll try to dig up the exact issue this weekend when I hit home and
let you all know.

The gist.  A ship inside another ship should automatically be assumed
to be within a 10 diameter sphere.  Thus it should automatically
misjump.  Yes, a tiny ship theoretically does create enough of a
gravity for itself that anything inside of it can be assumed to be
within 10 diameters.

A ship trying to jump from inside a ship which is in jump will be
destroyed.  I think that DGP stated as their logic that somewhere
way-back-when (TM) Marc Miller said that it couldn\'t be done because of
the way jump-physics worked.  A nice GM might just have the jump drive
melt itself or something instead of everyone becoming instant toast.

Hope this helps.

       --Jerry

