I found this interesting in that a number of previous posts have said that
canon required jumps to be to/from certain gravity densities, i.e. Jump 1
could only jump to the largest gravity well within a system, Jump 2 could
choose that or the next largest gravity well, etc.

Yet the ship-in-ship declaration seems to say the gravity of a single ship
is sufficient to upset jump and, therefore by extrapolation, sufficient to
act as a jump-to point?

