First, I just want to say that I got TTC #8 and your stuff was
fantastic!

But, if I remember correctly, the jumping into gravity wells is not
part of the Jump Institute\'s canon.  Jumping is not a method of travel
of going great distances as long as the entry and exit point have the
same gravitic densities.

Trying to be parsimonious, jump is entering jumpspace and coming out at
some other point a week later.  The only restrictions should be that
you should be 100 diameters out to jump safely, and you should be 100
diameters out just to be on the safe side when you arrive.  Misjumps
may (and will in some instances) occur if you don\'t meet some of the
safety criteria.

Hope this helps.

