The suggestion holds whether the limit is (magnitude of grav field) or (rate
of 
change of grav field) 
I\'m sure they would if they could -- I suspect that the "grav" field induced
by 
"grav" generators is either:

a) not "pucka" - only a pseudo-gravity which will prevent things flying
around 
by accelerating them in a certain direction
	(a parallel would be mag. fields which can be used to levitate things
	which respond to magnetism)   
or
b) the grav generator uses osscillators to make the field (or transform it)
and 
produces a rippling field whose average is the desired value, but the 
combination of riplles and peaks/troughs in the field make it still dangerous
to 
jump (or <grin> even MORE dangerous)

Based on physics, I\'d say (a), as Gravity seems to be intimately linked with
the 
curvature of space and the presence of matter and energy and probably
impossible 
to change, but we could find some force (the rumoured Fifth Force?) which
could 
accellerate things in a pseudo-gravitic manner while reatingin the curvature
of 
space.

>From a technology standpoint (b) looks "plausible", and has interesting game

implications -- can you jump if caught in a Tractor/Repulsor beam?
