According to DGP, artificial gravity does not eliminate
mass, it only negates the effects of gravity. AG is NOT
anti-grav, but a field inside which effects of gravity are
negated. And btw - you don\'t need to put grav plates in the
ceiling to get an upwards pull. Grav plates are perfectly
able to create pulls in every direction inside their area of
influence.

But then again, you\'re discussing a non-canonic variant
of the Traveller universe already :-)

Mark Seemann
ms@oem.dk
