There is nothing anywhere to state that Imperial space automatically
forms a single, closed sphere around all the perimeter stars of the
Empire, thereby enclosing and containing all stars that are not members
of the Empire as well. The non-member star systems themselves can
constitute a sphere (per system) that is NOT Imperial space, thereby
leaving those stars out of the Empire. In other words, the structure
of the Empire does not have to be a single, unbroken sphere of space.
Therefore, any peoples of non-member stars are not in Imperial space,
and do not have to be accorded the rights of an Imperial citizen.

This only handles part of the problem, and does not address what 
happens when those individuals actually enter Imperial space (through
visits, etc.). The quote you mentioned does not state how LONG that
a person has to be in Imperial space, just that they have to be IN it.

Bruce Rabalais
