    'body' => '> Date: Wed, 13 Sep 1995 16:04:54 -0400 (EDT)
> From: Glenn Myers <gem188@fea1.ansys.com>
> Subject: Fusion Power

  One thing that has bugged me is that in the Book 2 designs, the amount of 
fuel that a power-plant uses, depends on the ship it is in!
	a Type-A in the Scout uses 20tons in 4 weeks
	a Type-A in the Free Trader uses 10tons in 4 weeks
  What I\'ve done to fix this, is to produce a table relating fuel 
consumption to drive type (a-z), this is in line with the modular nature 
of Book 2 designs.
  This has been combined with a table of fuel consumption rates found in 
the "Beltstrike" module, again slightly modified.

  How they work.
	The fussion power plant, uses a magnetic bottle to contain the 
fussion plasma.  The fussion reaction chain is similar to the H-N-O-C 
chains in stellar fussion.  This is so my plants can use unrefined fuel 
straight from the tanks.
	The manoeuver drive, uses a mix of waste products from the 
fussion plant, and raw fuel itself.  These are mixed and fed to an MHD 
rocket.  The mixing of the fuel and fussion waste produces an ionised 
plasma mix, this is accellerated by the MHD coils and vented out of the 
exaust.

	This of course is the main reaction drive system.  There are 
other subsystems.  The low thrust manoeuvering, and the gravitic lift 
systems as well.

Alun
