3/10-95 Erwin Fritz wrote:

>This subject may have been brought up before, so forgive
>me if it has.  In the MegaTraveller combat rules, I can\'t find
>any reference to any sort of penalty for an unskilled use of
>a weapon in direct fire or indirect fire combat.  In >hand-to-hand combat
ther
e is a penalty though.
>
>Is this realistic?  It seems to me that it\'d be pretty strange if
>Joe Caveman picked up a nearby ACR and started
>blasting away with it.

Combat in MegaTraveller is task-based like most dice-
rolling is in that game. This means that the standard rules
for tasks are in effect with combat tasks too.

Unless a task has the "(unskilled ok)" qualifier, the task is
meant to be performed by skilled individuals. If the person
attempting the task does not have the skill, the difficulty
level of the task automatically increases by one.

For example, if (skillless) Joe Caveman picks up the ACR,
the normal "to hit" task may be routine, but Joe has to try to
make a difficult task with only his dex as a DM - a severe
penalty!

Mark Seemann
ms@oem.dk
