    'from' => 'Joseph L Lockett',
    'year' => 1995,
    'index' => 'ab804',
    'body' => 'So spake Erich Schneider: 
> DOMINATUS HOMINIS SPLENDET SPLENDIDE AMPLIUS QUAM GLORIAM ASTRIBUS

"The Rule of Man will shine brightly to the stars, more fully than (our?)
glory."

I myself would have said "AMPLIVS QVAM GLORIAM ASTRVM," "more fully than
the glory _of_ the stars," which would seem to make more sense.  But perhaps
there aren\'t as many Latin scholars about in 2610....

Speaking of which, I\'ve been working on-and-off on a historical campaign
set amid the Interstellar Wars, using 2300 AD\'s Near Star Map and the
excellent list available of correspondences between Traveller\'s 2D map
and the actual stars (whose author, alas, I forget).  Are there any good
"historical" references on 21st century Terra and the Solomani-Vilani
contact/conflict beyond the Classic supplements 8, 10, and 11 ("Library
Data" & "Solomani Rim"), Alien Module 6, and the MegaTraveller "Solomani &
Aslan"?  I also suspect that DGP\'s introduction of the belated "Plague of 
Duskir" would have shown up earlier, possibly provoking an ethical crisis
among the Terran Secretariat, and some economic theorizing ("Do we need
all these Vilani to support the war effort, or do we care if they all die
of rhinoviri and strep?").  When it\'s more presentable I\'ll announce a
Web page -- it\'ll probably use a bastardization of GURPS rules with
tech designs from TNE\'s FF&S and more-or-less standard Traveller
astronomic information.


