    'body' => '
erich@bush.cs.tamu.edu (Erich Schneider) wrote:
>I was wondering if any of you who have more Latin than I (my high
>school Latin teachers are undoubtedly tsk-ing right now) might
>translate the motto on the 2610 Rule of Man quarter-credit coin in the
>Solomani Alien Module. It appears to be:


DOMINATUS HOMINIS SPLENDET SPLENDIDE AMPLUS QUAM GLORIAM ASTRIBUS

The AMPLUS seems to have some odd spacing going on that almost looks
like an "I".  My high school Latin is horribly rusty, but it might
translate freely to something like

HOW GLORIOUS THE MIGHTY RULE OF MAN SPLENDIDLY GLEAMS WITH STARS

which seems to fit with the Zeus-and-Galaxy clutching lightning bolts
(and a dagger?) on the obverse of the coin.  It\'s been a while, so
I may be seriously scrambling the word order changes....  

There\'s some interesting place names in the Marches that may have
meaning in Latin.  Regina means queen, and it\'s a beautiful world 
that\'s very powerful in the sector.  Mora means delay or stop-off, 
and Mora is the gateway to the sector, a place settled as a base
for ships to stop-over as they enter the Marches.  Vilis means 
cheap or worthless -- but the Sword Worlders don\'t think so, and 
have gone to war with the Imperium (another Latin word!) over it.

  Steve Bonneville
  <bonn0015@tc.umn.edu>
  
