Based upon DGP\'s Starship Operator\'s Manual: Nothing happens. It\'s shut
down almost immediately after transition. Once you\'re in jump, only damage
to the lanthanum hull grid (which is used to create the jump bubble)
remains at a charged quantum state, and decays after about a week.

If you damage the grid, you could be exposed to the nature of jump space,
which tends to drive sapient carbon based life forms insane.

Jump is a deterministic event: your fate is determined when the ship first
transitions: Where you are going and when you\'ll arrive; and also if you\'ll
experience different time than the universe as a whole. And it only lasts a
minute or two!

Damaging the hull grid is a great way of eliminating a ship\'s crew and
passengers, though. They\'ll be insane before they drop out if you can
damage the grid enough. Just make certain you\'re not aboard...

Happy trails!

-Wil

