    'from' => 'Mark Cook markc@PEAK.ORG',
    'topic' => 'HIWG docs. available by ftp...',
    'body' => 'After a recent request by Andy Lilly, I\'ve just moved my spotty collection
of HIWG (History of the Imperium Working Group) documents, plus some other
assorted GDW & DGP material, onto the old (but still active) TML archive.

There are 2 collections of Traveller/HIWG data files, all of which have
been culled from the talk forums and library archives on GEnie.

 From the talk groups (the "BBS" directory), the files are:
  COACC.leftovers     - Some COACC designs that didn\'t make it into the
                        COACC pub.
  HIWG.sec_creation   - Discussion on developing a sector for HIWG.
  HIWG.structure      - Discussion of HIWG officers and document lists.
  MT.Q_n_A            - Questions & Answers from the GDW/DGP staff about MT.
  MT.aliens           - Discussion of Traveller alien races.
  MT.black_globes     - Discussion of black globes.
  MT.hardware         - Discussion of Traveller hardware and how to design
                        more.  (including list of MT hardware, most of which
                        isn\'t in any of the formal GDW publications.)
  MT.nuc_dampers      - Discussion of nuclear dampers.
  MT.plot_ideas       - Self-explanatory.
  MT.rebellion        - Discussion of the Traveller rebellion.
  MT.robots.cyborgs   - Discussion of the _Robots_&_Cyborgs_ project (which
                        never got off the ground.  I suspect much of this
                        ended up in the New Era.)
  MT.sci_n_tech       - Discussion of science & tech. in the MT universe.
  MT.starports        - Discussion of MT starports.
  MT.starship_builder - Discussion about the creation of the MT _Starship_
                        _Builders_Handbook_.

 From the GDW/HIWG library (the "Lib" directory), the files are:
  Aslan           - Cultural article on the Aslan race.
  Deep_Shadows    - A MegaTraveller adventure scenario.
  HIWG.doc_list   - A complete list of available HIWG documents, as of
6/23/90.
  Julian_Protect  - Cultural article on the Julian Protectorate.
  MT.Vland_docs   - List of HIWG docs. concerning Vland and the Vilani.
  MT.lib          - List of the contents of the GEnie Traveller library, as
                    of 3/11/91.
  MT.tasks        - A canonical list of all task descriptions from the
                    following MT sourcebooks:
                      Mega-Traveller Players Manual
                      Mega-Traveller Imperial Encyclopedia
                      Mega-Traveller Referee\'s Manual
                      Rebellion Sourcebook
                      Mega-Traveller Referee\'s Companion
                      Starship Operator\'s Manual Vol 1
                      COACC
  Nuc_fusion      - Technical study of nuclear fusion, as it relates to
                    MegaTraveller.
  REFT.Sector     - The complete UWP listing for the Reft sector.
  REFT.Sector.rev - The revised UWP listing for the Reft sector (w/ updated
                    information from Travellers Digest #20.)
  Sirir           - A MegaTraveller adventure scenario.
  TNS.items       - The collected TNS articles (as posted in Challenge
                    magazine) from the dates 097-1105 to 238-1119.
  answerin.txt    - Article (physical & cultural) on the Answerin race.
  cafadi.txt      - Article (physical & cultural) on the Cafadi race.
  irhadre.txt     - Article (physical & cultural) on the Irhadre race.
  jgd_il_jagd     - An MT adventure scenario involving the Jgd-Il-Jagd race.
  mil_policies    - A treatise on Vilani military thought.
  minor_races     - A (supposedly) canonical list of MT minor races.
  tapazmal.txt    - Article (physical & cultural) on the Tapazmali race.
  thaggesh.txt    - Article (physical & cultural) on the Thaggesh race.
  world_names     - List of all world names as they have appeared in any
                    authorized Traveller-related publication or article.

To download any of these files, ftp to ftp.engrg.uwo.ca and look in the
directory ~/pub/traveller/HIWG.

        - Mark C.

