    'body' => 'Responding to Hyperodge.

Hi.  I forgot a couple of things in my answers to your questions.  First 
of all, when aiming for a ship in its "bubble" of possible locations, one 
only cares about a plane through the bubble perpendicular to the 
direction of fire (yeesh, I\'m technobabbling again).  What I mean is, if 
you were looking at the bubble, you would see a circle.  That is the area 
in question, since the laser beams you fire will travel all the way 
through the bubble\'s "depth dimension" anyway.  I\'m not sure I\'m 
explaining this very well, please let me know.

Secondly, is the space combat system you are developing for use during 
role-playing?  I\'d like to know a little more about it.  Space combat 
systems are a particular interest of mine. If the system is to be used 
during role-playing, then I encourage you to include some kind of agility 
roll for the pilot to make.  One thing that the Traveller space combat 
systems I\'ve seen tend to leave out is the pilot factor.

Bye for now,
Charles.

