    'body' => 'Tom Trelenberg (ex-lurker?) asks (paraphrased):

"Can you crash-land an unstreamlined ship on a world?"

Nasty stuff atmosphere - makes your ship all hot and requires streamlining
to maneouvre once you\'ve got through the outer bit and cooled down a bit.
Well, dense atmosphere will burn you up then rip you apart for definite,
since an unstreamlined ship doesn\'t have the necessary heat-shielding and
fuselage shaping to withstand the atmospheric effects. Thin or trace
atmosphere gives you a chance because the heat-up will be much less and the
aerodynamic drag should be less so you might not get ripped apart. Given the
latter option I\'d do the following (to make the players feel they\'ve earned
their survival rather than just been allowed to land because you need it for
the plot...)

