    'body' => '>support it\'s own weight.  I figure if a ship can survive hits from
>missiles which will knock it around at over 10 Gs, it can survive

What kind of missiles are you talking about? Take a look at Special
Supplement 3 - Missiles, and you\'ll find out that starship missile payloads
are relatively WEAK things... the missiles are 15x100cm, and mostly
propulsion. Non nuclear missiles get 2-4 hits per 10 kg of explosive. CT
missiles are not allowed to exceed 50 kg, so you could get about 45kg on
the slowest, stupidest missile allowed for a turret launcher. That won\'t
throw a 100ton vessel around at even 1 g, let alone at 10g\'s. Simple
momentum-mass-conservation_of_energy factors at work here.


