Earth is constantly being hit with several tons per week of miniscule
debris. (more probable, but I don\'t have the figures handy) Vaporization of
a whole cloud of chunks is MUCH less of a disaster than one big thud, which
adds vibrational, impact, and dust effects. And an explosion that can break
it will spread the parts out.

>For example, the million gee version will dump approximatelly 500
>megatons into what it hits. That\'s enough to *kill* all unshielded
>personnel on that side of the planet, and change global weather
>patterns. It\'s also not certain that pieces travelling at 1.5% of c
