I think you are making a round-off error. the velocity doesn\'t increase 
in steps of 2 m/s, it increases continuously over time. 
eg at t=3 sec x= 0.5 * 2 * 3^2 = 9 meters.
why not just use that good ole\' formula from high-school physics:

x= (1/2)*Acceleration*(Time^2) + InitialVelocity*Time +Initial position.  ?
 
and yes, you can assume no initial vector for the sake of argument, 
although keep in mind that it will affect the apparent shape of 
the "probable position bell".

although the manual method is accurate enough for a game - it\'s just 
more grunge-work.


cheers,
