    'body' => 'Several people mentioned that jump missiles are impractical because (in 
CT/MT) they would have to be 100+ tons.  But that depends on the nature 
of the 100 ton limit.  I\'m sure someone will pound me with a bunch of 
canonical references about this, but AFAIK there are three possible 
reasons for the 100 ton limit:

1. The jumping object must be 1400 m^3 in volume but can be any mass.  If
this is the case, then one could have the jump missile as an unfolding or
inflating sort of thing with a tiny jump drive, powerplant and fuel tank to
carry the reduced mass into jump space.  Of course this doesn\'t work if 
you assume the size of the j-drive is dependent on the volume of the 
jumping object, so you have to make some pretty "convenient" assumptions.

2. The jumping object must be 100 tons in weight but can be any volume.  
In this case, it is easy to pack the missile full of lead (I know, it\'s a 
silly image, but bear with me) and it could be reasonably small.  Again, 
you have to make some pretty convenient assumptions about the basis for 
jump drive size etc.  There is also another question:  does the ship 
carrying this super-dense missile 
have to set aside 100 tons of space for it?  The lack of a volume/mass 
distinction in CT makes this hard to resolve.

3. The jumping object must satisfy both of the above conditions.  In that 
case, there is no hope for reasonably small jump missiles.

There is also a fourth (decidedly non-canonical) interpretation:  the 100 
tons limit is due to human limitations, not physical ones.  I\'ve pictured 
this as a problem of the bizarre physics of jump space intruding on the 
ship.  People on small ships get disorientation and nausea entering jump 
space due to these effects.  The bigger the ship, the more of a 
"stabilizing" effect it has on the jump space around it.  Below 100 tons, 
the effects become dangerous, causing epilepsy-like spasms and sometimes 
death.  In this case jump missiles are no problem, and people willing to 
risk injury and death can take smaller ships into jump space if they wish.
You could have groups of super-elite pilots who happen to be 
jump-resistant taking jump-fighters through and so on.  This sort of 
thing would have profound effects on the game universe, I think, as would 
jump missiles.

Charles.

