    'body' => 'Hi again

Charles Collin provided some useful information about the intensity of a 
painful-to-look at flash, and also said that the flare would indicate the 
rough size of the emerging vessel.  I\'m not sure about this second point; 
isn\'t the "blinding" flash just the initial bright point of light before 
the thing fills out to allow the vessel through.  In that case, the 
bright flash may not depend to any great degree on the size of the 
emerging vessel, it is just a metre-square (for example) so always 
represents the same initial energy burst.  Also note that the SOM 
description is from the point of view of someone watching the vessel, so 
will not include information about effects at other wavelengths or on 
other physical effects (gravity, neutrinos, etc.)  As jump appears to be 
linked in some manner to gravity (the 100 diameter rule), then perhaps 
there will be some noticable gravitational effect, as I think someone has 
already said.

