Internet=(xboat@mpgn.com)

7/11-95 Rodge wrote:

>Even though a "jump missile" might be impossible, surely
>a starship could be converted into an unmanned
>kamakazi device -- in practical terms, a jump missile.

If you want to stick very closely to canon, then no, it can\'t be
done. Let me elaborate a little on this.

Apparently, canon is not one thing, but many, on this
subject. Old CT sources are at odds with MT sources like
SOM and the writings of Joe Fugate on the subject (both in
TD and on GEnie). In MT you can\'t easily use your jump
fuel to make two jump-1s in stead of one jump-2, for
example. The description of the jump drive itself is also
different. So what is canon depends on which game you
are playing.

In MT, starships cannot be remote controlled or automated,
according to answers by Joe Fugate to some questions
posed on GEnie. He doesn\'t explain why, and it never
made sense to me. In my campaign, it is at least possible
to guide a ship into jump via remote, because that makes
sense to me. But it isn\'t canon.

If you allow remote controlling of jumps, then the "jump
missile" mentioned above is possible. But it would still
have to be 100+ tons and have a fully functional jump drive
and computer. Not a very cheap jump missile, and it
requires a rather large ship to be carried on board. Not
very practical, in my opinion.

Mark Seemann
ms@oem.dk
