    'topic' => 'world generation',
    'body' => 'I understand the world generation procedure in general, but I was wondering:
just what kind of worlds does this generation system make? It seems that most
of the worlds will have populations of some kind, of widely varying tech
levels. These are obviously meant to be civilized worlds rather than new,
unexplored areas. Are these meant to be worlds in the Imperium? Worlds in the
process of being colonized and brought up to Imperium-level technology?
Worlds "left over" from the Long Night (with some having experienced a large
drop in tech level).  I\'m sure that some populations may be minor human races
or aliens, but not all. Should there be some kind of modifier for different
types of worlds? Say for example that worlds that have been explored for the
first time are not likely to have any populations at all.  Worlds being
colonized will have a minimum tech level needed for colonization, depending
on the environmental conditions on the world. Mature worlds will have a tech
level closer to an Imperial standard--unless the residents decide
differently.
Suggestions anyone?
