Personally, I think that Dulinor would have finally managed to seize 
Capital (remember that last fleet he sent to Capital?  Without Virus, I 
think he would have pulled it off.).  

However, it would have taken decades - possibily as long as 70 
years - until the Imperial Core had recovered enough to try to take on 
Vland and the Domain of Delphi.

The Domain of Deneb would have become either a formal monarchy or a 
republic.  Archduke Brkz was blown up - which led to the rapid 
disintergration of the League of Antares.  Probably, the area would have 
become a part of the Julian Protectorate.  The "Domain of Delphi" (aka 
Margraet\'s stronghold) and the Daibei Federation would have stabilized, 
and may have become rather powerful if the Solomani Confederation was as 
weak as is sometimes thought.  

Note: Archduchess Margaret bore twins, one of which was a clone(?) of 
Strephon.  The Domain of Delphi and Dulinor\'s Imperium would be at odds, 
probably leading to a new war.

The Vegans were well on there way to being conquered by the late 1120\'s.  
However, it may have regained it\'s freedom if the Solomani fractured as 
badly as people on TML/XTML seem to feel.  I persponally suspect that the 
Solomani would have simply reconquered it\'s Sphere, and then focused it\'s 
expansion efforts rimwards.

The Domain of Deneb would have been somewhat deal smaller than the Regency 
at 1200.  By the time the fighting there stopped, all Imperial holdings 
in Trojan Reach and Reft Sector would have been lost, although more of 
Deneb would have been recovered, at least to Segan. 

(sorry, but I\'m  following offical GDW history regarding the Aslan/Vargr 
ivasions, rather than admitting that - given our knowledge of their 
demographics and technology - any such invasion is impossible)

Very few pocket empires (The Covenant of Sufren, maybe?) would have 
survived the Short Dusk.  The Real Strephon wouldn\'t have, as it\'s bones were
being picked on by more and more raiders - including Star Vikings - by 1130.


