Because when Traveller was written (in the 70\'s), the understanding of
antimatter (particularly by game writers) was considerably less than
it is now?  It\'s one of those quirks that populate the Classic Traveller
universe.

>  Actually, it would be a matter (no pun intended) of _containing_ the stuff
>  [...] You can\'t build something out of promatter to attach your antimatter
>  [...] You need fields that have all of the properties of matter except for
>  the physicality and they have to be not only airtight, but totally
