I don\'t know about all psionic powers, but - in most cases -
a neural acitivity sensor will be able to detect a telepath.
"WHAT?!" you may say, "a telepath is shielded and there-
fore invisible to a NAS." Quite so. This means that if some-
one is right in front of you and not wearing a psionic shield
helmet, and he or she doesn\'t show on a NAS, then this
person is either dead or or a telepath. Methods exists to
determine if the person is dead or not :-)

In one of my current campaigns, one of the PCs is a
telepath (one of her talents). After she found out the above
fact, she\'s often walking around with her shield down. The
risk of being discovered as a psionicist by a "normal"
imperial citizen is much greater than the risk of meeting a
hostile psionicist.

Wether there are other ways to detect psionics other than
the lenghty test performed by a psionics institute I don\'t
know.

