    'index' => 'ac153',
    'body' => '"Francis, Edgar (G) Islamic Std" <francise@others.sscnet.ucla.edu> writes:

> own conversions.  Of course, that\'s if you can find and afford them.  I saw a
> copy of _Droyne_ going for $22 at a con last year!  (Does anybody know what
> copyright laws are for materials that are out of print?)

Same as for materials that are in print. Generally, in most of the
world, that means that the copyright is good for 75 years for stuff
copyrighted by a corporation, and good for 50-75 years *after the death
of the author* for stuff copyrighted by an individual.

So not only is no Traveller related material out of copyright, none is
*likely* to be until the mid 21st century!

Even if a company has gone out of business, the rights are held by
*someome*. And you need to track that someone down to get permission.

