    'day' => '09',
    'from' => 'Glenn M. Goffin',
    'year' => 1995,
    'index' => 'ac173',
    'body' => 'World Builder\'s Handbook, page 11, describes the Neural Activity Sensor
("NAS") (available at TL 12) as "detect[ing] the electrical activity of a
life form\'s central nervous system and classif[ying] it according to amount
and complexity."  The NAS can indicate number, range, and motion to beings
exhibiting neural activity.

It can show brain pattern readings of simple, complex, and cluttered.

Neural classes are unknown, human/vargr, aslan, droyne, k\'kree, hiver, and
other (i.e., a minor race the NAS is programmed to recognize).

Intelligence readings are lower form (e.g., worms, insects, fish), not
intelligent (e.g., cattle, birds, bees), semi-intelligent (e.g. dogs, apes,
not uplifted dolphins), and intelligent ("Very complex brain functions
characteristic of sentient life").

These readings are not on a very fine scale, but quite gross.

(Have the EEGs of humans and other large-brained mammals actually been
compared?  I wonder if, e.g., a cow\'s brain really uses less electricity
than a human\'s.)

Imperial Encyclopedia, page 63, describes the Psionic Shield Helmet ("PSH")
as a "Battery powered helmet creating a weak electrical field at human
brainwave frequencies; psionic-talented individuals perceive this as static,
whic prevents undesirable telepathic influences or psionic assaults."  PSH
is only effective against telepathy and related abilities; it has no effect
on, e.g., telekinesis.

WBHB doesn\'t address the impact on psionics.  My approach has been as follows:

Assume that every psychological state has at least one physiological
correlative state.

NAS doesn\'t detect psionic ability, because (1) mere possession of the
ability does not use electrical impulses (like knowing a foreign language
doesn\'t involve electrical impulses until the subject begins to use the
language) or (2) brains vary too much and/or NAS is not sensitive enough to
distinguish between different electrical states and determine that a certain
state indicates "speaking French" versus "using telekinesis".  NAS
technology may be able to make such distinctions as to a single subject
after extensive mapping.

NAS doesn\'t detect that a brain is using psionics, for the second reason
that it does not detect psionic ability.

NAS directed at an individual wearing a PSH detects all of the individual\'s
neuro-electrical activity, allowing the full panoply of gross readings given
above.  PSH scrambles the brainwave readings in a characteristic fashion, so
the NAS will detect that PSH is operating.

--Glenn

