    'body' => 'Dear Folks -

Bri asked:

> I was wondering, during CT times, what did the Imperial Navy look like
>size(disp) and size(# of) wise?

I think that to get an accurate "canonical" picture you need the following
resources:
        1. Fifth Frontier War
        2. The Spinward Marches Campaign
        3. MT Rebellion Sourcebook

The 5FW shows the size of fleets in one major battle. SMC gives you an actual
breakdown of ships in one battle-rider squadron, whose counter actually appears
in the 5FW game. Finally, MT-REBEL gives a picture of the number of fleets
across the entire Imperium.

A supplementary source is Trillion Credit Squadron (for economies and naval
budgets). Remember, though, there was an earlier discussion on this list about
the Navy. I think that I said something about the ratio of supporting
infrastructure to the number of actual craft; AIR it was something horrible
like 10:1 (ie. only 10% of the budget is used to actually buy AND maintain
ships).

- Hyphen
(David Jaques-Watson)

