    'year' => 1995,
    'from' => 'sudet@well.com',
    'body' => 'Have we had these discussions before?

A) How do you fellow Travellers pronounce the following:
Efate (I\'ve usually heard F-8)
Ine Givar (I\'ve usually heard eenay zhi\'-var, but often ine giv\'-ar with
a hard "g")
Boughene
Moughas

B) What is the truth about the Ine Givar?  There seems to be a dearth of
canon about them.  I\'ve usually used the following in my campaigns, but
solicit your ideas and criticisms:

1.  "Ine Givar" is a label that the Imperial government uses to demonize
any internal enemy in the Spinward Marches or Corridor sectors.
Accusations of Ine Givar activity invoke certain anti-Ine Givar laws,
giving additional prosecutorial and investigative powers to Imperial
military and naval intelligence.  In addition, the population of the
region has long been conditioned to respond with fear and hatred to the
Ine Givar.

2.  The Ine Givar is a large cadre of revolutionaries operating primarily
in the spinward/coreward regions of the Imperium.  Its goal is to liberate
the region from Imperial/megacorp/noble domination and establish a free
state governed by the residents of the various worlds according to their
own needs and desires.  The Ine Givar is largely pro-psionic and some
branches receive funding from the Zhodani Consulate.  Outside control is a
constant, and divisive, issue within the Ine Givar leadership.  The Ine
Givar cadre devote considerable resources to training revolutionaries on
various worlds; the cadre itself, while large, is still small compared to
the population of a sector (maybe 100,000 - 200,000).

3.  1 and 2 are both true.

If anyone can cite me to canonical discussion of the Ine Givar, I would
be grateful.

--Glenn
