>Steve Bonneville,
>In Xboat digest 470, you commented on various races\' behaviors during the
>civil war, and mentioned the K\'kree:
>>The K\'kree are too far away -- their jump drive technology probably
>> lagged the Imperium even worse in the 600s than it does in the >1100s.
>
>Can you elaborate a bit on this, and on where you got info on the K\'kree
>lagging in jump tech? Are they a jump number or two behind in 1100, for
>example?  I don\'t recall discussion of this in Alien Module 2.
>

Really simple to figure: K\'Kree max TL is 14 (module 2), Imperial is TL 15
(with a few worlds being either isolationist tl 16-17, or emergent tl 16 in
a few fields). Under Bk 5: High Gurad, and all later Traveller design
structures, the following limits are in force:

TL      Max J-n
15+     6
14      5
13      4
12      3
11      2
9-10    1

Thus K\'Kree max TL 14 indicates a J-5 max, while Imperial max TL 15
indicates a J-6 max. Figuring 35 jumps per year maximum operational speed,
that\'s a full sector of difference! Realize also that the K\'Kree structure
of government has fewer levels, and less interstellar autonomy, so
decisions need to be made closer to home in terms of turn around time, so
the k\'kree would operate closer to home.

-Wil

